  10 Nov 2002; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> evolution-1.1.90.ebuild :
  Update some USE flags.  Add patches from Mandrake.

*evolution-1.1.90 (9 Nov 2002)

  9 Nov 2002; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> evolution-1.1.90.ebuild :
  Added RC1.

*evolution-1.0.8-r2 (16 Oct 2002)

  16 Oct 2002; foser <foser@gentoo.org> evolution-1.0.8-r2.ebuild :
  Added a patch which fixes bug #5373
 
*evolution-1.0.8-r1 (20 Jul 2002)

  28 Aug 2002; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> evolution-1.0.8-r1.ebuild :
  Add scrollkeeper to DEPEND.

  20 Aug 2002; Mark Guertin <gerk@gentoo.org> evolution-1.0.8-r1.ebuild :
  Put scrollkepper within doc?() in DEPEND to prevent it from trying to pull
  All the doc stuff, even with USE="-doc" (also a nasty bug in docbook-sgml-utils
  is stopping people from using because of this)

  20 Jul 2002; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> :
  Fix $D being hardcoded into the binary in some cases (ccache ??).

*evolution-1.0.8 (17 Jul 2002)

  17 Jul 2002; Gabriele Giorgetti <stroke@gentoo.org> evolution-1.0.8.ebuild:

  New version and updated dependencies.


*evolution-1.0.7 (15 Jun 2002)

  15 Jun 2002; Gabriele Giorgetti <stroke@gentoo.org> evolution-1.0.7.ebuild:

  New version

*evolution-1.0.5-r3 (12 Jun 2002)

  12 Jun 2002; Gabriele Giorgetti <stroke@gentoo.org> evolution-1.0.5-r3.ebuild :

  Updated dep to the new gtkhtml revision. Bug #3659 related.


*evolution-1.0.5-r2 (09 Jun 2002)

  09 Jun 2002; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> :

  Use the new "elibtoolize" function from libtool.eclass.  Hopefully this
  will fix the pda and libtoolize problems.

*evolution-1.0.5-r1 (09 Jun 2002)
  
  09 Jun 2002; Gabriele Giorgetti <stroke@gentoo.org> evolution-1.0.5-1.ebuild :

  Updated dependencies. Changed deps to work even if gnome2 is unmasked.
  Also this should Close/Fixe bug #3444
 
*evolution-1.0.5 (13 May 2002)

  13 May 2002; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> evolution-1.0.5.ebuild :

  Updated version.

*evolution-1.0.3-r7 (03 May 2002) 
  03 May 2002; Spider <spider@gentoo.org> evolution-1.0.3-r7.ebuild :
  Adding an important security fix

  as reported on the mailing list yesterday, Evolution 1.0.3 has a serious
  bug that can make it eat all the memory on your system and then crash
  when downloading certain messages with invalid headers.
  
  29 Apr 2002; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> evolution-1.0.3-r6.ebuild :

  Replaced the "perl" use flag with "doc".

*evolution-1.0.3-r6 (23 Apr 2002)

  23 Apr 2002; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> evolution-1.0.3-r6.ebuild :

  Resolve bug #334.  Note: libtoolize is run only if "pda" is not in USE.

*evolution-1.0.3-r5 (22 Apr 2002)

  22 Apr 2002; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> evolution-1.0.3-r6.ebuild :

  Resolve bug #334.

*evolution-1.0.3-r4 (13 Apr 2002)
  13 Apr 2002; Spider <spider@gentoo.org> evolution-1.0.3-r4.ebuild :
  Adding a dependency on gob in a futile attempt to solve bug #1674
  

*evolution-1.0.3-r3 (9 April 2002)

  09 Apr 2002; M.Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> evolution-1.0.3-r3.ebuild :

